title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\VmEndpointNatMappingsInterfaceNatMappings
name: VmEndpointNatMappingsInterfaceNatMappings
description:
Contain information of Nat mapping for an interface of this endpoint.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.VmEndpointNatMappingsInterfaceNatMappings

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.drain_nat_ip_port_ranges
params.description: List of all drain IP:port-range mappings assigned to this interface. These ranges are inclusive, that is, both the first and the last ports can be used for NAT. Example: ["2.2.2.2:12345-12355", "1.1.1.1:2234-2234"].

params.name: data.nat_ip_port_ranges
params.description: A list of all IP:port-range mappings assigned to this interface. These ranges are inclusive, that is, both the first and the last ports can be used for NAT. Example: ["2.2.2.2:12345-12355", "1.1.1.1:2234-2234"].

params.name: data.num_total_drain_nat_ports
params.description: Total number of drain ports across all NAT IPs allocated to this interface. It equals to the aggregated port number in the field drain_nat_ip_port_ranges.

params.name: data.num_total_nat_ports
params.description: Total number of ports across all NAT IPs allocated to this interface. It equals to the aggregated port number in the field nat_ip_port_ranges.

params.name: data.rule_mappings
params.description: Information about mappings provided by rules in this NAT.

params.name: data.source_alias_ip_range
params.description: Alias IP range for this interface endpoint. It will be a private (RFC 1918) IP range. Examples: "10.33.4.55/32", or "192.168.5.0/24".

params.name: data.source_virtual_ip
params.description: Primary IP of the VM for this NIC.
